<TITLE> Danish climate minister to arrive Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 1 (bdnews24.com)Danish minister for climate and energy Connie Hedegaard will arrive in Bangladesh on Monday for a two-day official visit, according to the Danish embassy in Dhaka. The Danish minister will meet state minister for environment and forest Mostafizur Rahman, according to the programme circulated by the embassy. She will inquire about Bangladesh's preparedness for the climate change conference scheduled for Copenhagen by year-end. Environment ministry officials said she would visit Southern districts to view its vulnerability to climate change. Hedegaard will also meet with prime minister Sheikh Hasina and state minister for foreign affairs Hasan Mahmud to discuss global climate change challenges and Bangladesh's preparation, said a press release issued by the Danish embassy. Low-lying Bangladesh, located in the Ganges Delta, will be one of the countries worst affected by climate change. Denmark has pledged to contribute to a multi-donor trust fund for chalking out climate change mitigation and adaptation programmes in Bangladesh. bdn
